ntina has motivated individuals to seek nationality in ancestral homelands, thinking two nationalities would be more valuable than one. This book details the legal and administrative mechanisms at work, describes the patterns of law and practice, and explores the implications for how we understand the very meaning of citizenship.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aCitizenshipzArgentina. 0aCitizenshipzItaly. 0aCitizenshipzSpain. 0aDual nationalityzArgentina. 0aDual nationalityzItaly. 0aDual nationalityzSpain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804784757zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804784757423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804784757.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles